Subject: [PATCH 06/10] ubuntu: sysprep: Disable lvm-uuids when testing.

It fails like this:

sysprep operation failed: exception: Guestfs.Error("pvchange_uuid_all:   Volume group containing /dev/sda2 has active logical volumes")

Possibly related to broken udev rules in Ubuntu.
---
 sysprep/test-virt-sysprep.sh |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/sysprep/test-virt-sysprep.sh b/sysprep/test-virt-sysprep.sh
index 7c4660a..266d362 100755
--- a/sysprep/test-virt-sysprep.sh
+++ b/sysprep/test-virt-sysprep.sh
@@ -23,6 +23,7 @@ set -e
 operations=$(
   ./virt-sysprep --list-operations |
     fgrep '*' |
+    grep -v lvm-uuids |
     awk '{printf ("%s,",$1)}' |
     sed 's/,$//'
 )
